Doc# 20220139591 06/03/2022 02:17 PM Page 1 of 2 Lucy Adame-Clark, Bexar County Clerk
NOTICE OF LIEN AFFIDAVIT
STATE OF TEXAS
COUNTY OF BEXAR
As of June 3, 2022:
The undersigned, of the County of Bexar and State of Texas, the legal and equitable owner of a certain continuing lien for payment of
maintenance assessments to The St. Charles Association, Inc ., more fully described in the Declaration of Covenants, Conditions and
Restrictions, duly recorded in the Official Public Records of Real Property, Bexar County, Texas, against the following property, to wit:
SUBJECT PROPERTY:
16 S Rue Charles , San Antonio, TX 78217
LEGAL DESCRIPTION:
NCB 11977, BLK 2, LOT 50, THE SAINT
CHARLES
LAST KNOWN OWNER(S):
Allen V. Mueck
AMOUNT OF ARREARAGE AT FILING:
$6,694.54
CONTACT FOR AFFIDAVIT OF SATISFACTION:
Crist Law Firm, PLLC
3123 N.W. Loop 410
San Antonio, Texas 78230
(210) 340-3277
Affidavit filed for period up to and including June 3, 2022. Please contact the Association for actual payout. Amount due is subject to
the addition of interest, monthly accounting charges, and other fees and charges.
DATED: 3 June 2022
By:
THOMAS L. PLACIER
Attorney for the The St. Charles Association, Inc.
STATE OF TEXAS
COUNTY OF BEXAR
This instrument was acknowledged before me on the June 3, 2022, by Thomas L. Placier, attorney for The St. Charles
Association, Inc.
CHRISTOPHER D. MERIDITH
My Notary ID # 133106324
Expires May 18, 2025
AFTER RECORDING RETURN TO:
CRIST LAW FIRM, PLLC
3123 N. W. Loop 410
San Antonio, TX 78230
